1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:36,286
<i>You're smart.</i>

2
00:00:36,369 --> 00:00:38,997
<i>But what have you done?</i>
<i>You always say yes.</i>

3
00:00:39,080 --> 00:00:40,165
<i>You just keep charging ahead.</i>

4
00:00:40,248 --> 00:00:41,374
Why did you say that?

5
00:00:41,458 --> 00:00:43,251
Do you have to say it
aloud that I'm single?

6
00:00:43,334 --> 00:00:44,502
I'll be your date.

7
00:00:44,586 --> 00:00:45,545
<i>Ouch!</i>

8
00:01:02,020 --> 00:01:04,606
<i>After everything I found out from Sianong.</i>

9
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:13,823
You thought I would be easy to kill?

10
00:01:13,907 --> 00:01:15,158
You're caught now.

11
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:23,291
Dad, I want to protect her.

12
00:01:23,374 --> 00:01:24,667
From her family's world.

13
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:26,336
<i>You really think she knows nothing?</i>

14
00:01:26,419 --> 00:01:29,631
<i>You think Chiara doesn't know</i>
<i>the kind of world her parents live in?</i>

15
00:01:29,714 --> 00:01:32,467
- Sir, are you okay? Medic, medic!
- She escaped.

16
00:01:32,550 --> 00:01:34,344
- Medic!
- She escaped!

17
00:01:39,057 --> 00:01:40,558
I don't believe you, Dad.

18
00:01:40,642 --> 00:01:42,143
You're wrong about Chiara.

19
00:01:45,897 --> 00:01:48,650
Mikoy, I know you love her.

20
00:01:48,733 --> 00:01:51,069
Don't let yourself be blinded

21
00:01:51,152 --> 00:01:55,448
by your feelings for her
just to believe she's innocent.

22
00:01:55,532 --> 00:01:58,076
You saw Chiara yourself, Dad. Right?

23
00:01:58,159 --> 00:01:59,661
Shopping, going out.

24
00:01:59,744 --> 00:02:01,037
That's her only world.

25
00:02:02,122 --> 00:02:03,623
That's why it's hard to believe

26
00:02:03,706 --> 00:02:05,834
she's involved in her father's business.

27
00:02:10,088 --> 00:02:11,047
Dear,

28
00:02:11,631 --> 00:02:13,424
those kinds of syndicates,

29
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:16,594
they're family.

30
00:02:20,223 --> 00:02:21,933
Loyalty runs deep,

31
00:02:22,016 --> 00:02:23,560
that's why they're hard to take down.

32
00:02:24,102 --> 00:02:26,437
That's why I believe
Chiara knows something

33
00:02:27,021 --> 00:02:29,065
and I wouldn't be surprised if one day,

34
00:02:29,941 --> 00:02:33,736
she ends up inheriting
the syndicate her family runs.

35
00:03:03,892 --> 00:03:05,226
Check over there.

36
00:03:23,953 --> 00:03:25,747
Chiara is different, Dad.

37
00:03:26,539 --> 00:03:27,999
She's not like them.

38
00:03:48,645 --> 00:03:51,773
Dad, you just don't know
her well enough yet.

39
00:03:51,856 --> 00:03:53,483
That's why you think that way.

40
00:03:55,109 --> 00:03:58,613
Also, she could never do whatever horrible
things her father is capable of

41
00:03:58,696 --> 00:04:02,033
and she would never want
to enter the dirty world of her family.

42
00:04:08,414 --> 00:04:09,332
My son,

43
00:04:10,124 --> 00:04:13,211
no matter how kind she was to us, to you,

44
00:04:13,294 --> 00:04:16,172
that doesn't mean she's
incapable of becoming one of them.

45
00:04:17,715 --> 00:04:20,093
It doesn't mean she's not a Moraviano.

46
00:04:21,928 --> 00:04:23,513
But Dad, I know her.

47
00:04:24,889 --> 00:04:26,724
Chiara is a good person, Dad.

48
00:04:26,808 --> 00:04:28,518
She's not like that.

49
00:04:29,435 --> 00:04:30,395
Also Dad,

50
00:04:30,478 --> 00:04:32,730
how did you even find out all of this?

51
00:04:32,814 --> 00:04:36,401
Also, why do you have so many guns?

52
00:04:38,778 --> 00:04:40,238
Dad, what are you going to do?

53
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:45,618
Mikoy, I…

54
00:04:46,202 --> 00:04:47,412
I have a past.

55
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:52,292
Law enforcement, but I'm not the police.

56
00:04:53,418 --> 00:04:54,419
Are you a gangster too?

57
00:04:55,378 --> 00:04:56,504
I'm not a gangster.

58
00:04:57,297 --> 00:04:58,506
Intelligence asset.

59
00:05:00,425 --> 00:05:04,429
And that's when I started suspecting
especially after you got shot.

60
00:05:06,723 --> 00:05:08,599
I thought you were handling land deals.

61
00:05:08,683 --> 00:05:10,059
That was just my cover story.

62
00:05:11,602 --> 00:05:12,478
You're really something, Dad.

63
00:05:12,562 --> 00:05:14,230
So I could investigate this.

64
00:05:15,273 --> 00:05:18,067
So what happened was,
I tracked down one of my friends

65
00:05:18,151 --> 00:05:20,820
and he gave me information
about Viktor and the others.

66
00:05:25,992 --> 00:05:26,826
That's enough.

67
00:05:26,909 --> 00:05:28,161
It's not life-threatening.

68
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:29,787
Sir.

69
00:05:29,871 --> 00:05:31,372
- What?
- Sir.

70
00:05:31,456 --> 00:05:32,874
We've swept the entire area.

71
00:05:32,957 --> 00:05:35,335
The house is clear,
there are no more explosives.

72
00:05:36,419 --> 00:05:38,212
We cornered her.

73
00:05:38,963 --> 00:05:41,549
But, she had a plan B.

74
00:05:45,053 --> 00:05:46,512
She's not easy to corner.

75
00:05:46,596 --> 00:05:48,806
We'll catch her eventually, sir.

76
00:05:48,890 --> 00:05:50,808
We'll corner her again.

77
00:05:51,476 --> 00:05:52,769
Looks like she got hit,

78
00:05:52,852 --> 00:05:55,229
there's blood on her clothes, sir.

79
00:05:58,483 --> 00:06:00,401
- Yes, sir.
- Maybe we can identify her

80
00:06:00,485 --> 00:06:03,696
or maybe we already have
her record in the database.

81
00:06:08,826 --> 00:06:10,244
‪ALEXANDRIA CORTEZ
‪AGENT

82
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:27,136
<i>Alex…</i>

83
00:06:35,311 --> 00:06:37,647
And why should I trust you?

84
00:06:39,732 --> 00:06:41,567
I don't need your trust.

85
00:06:54,372 --> 00:06:55,915
Carlota called.

86
00:07:05,758 --> 00:07:06,634
Bok.

87
00:07:08,094 --> 00:07:09,387
There you go again.

88
00:07:11,139 --> 00:07:12,765
Don't trust her, okay?

89
00:07:12,849 --> 00:07:14,642
You already know that.

90
00:07:22,316 --> 00:07:24,360
That's what you've said
before about Mikoy.

91
00:07:26,404 --> 00:07:30,074
We're already here
and we've come this far because of that.

92
00:08:23,878 --> 00:08:25,129
This isn't Henry.

93
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:44,398
<i>Oh, please</i>

94
00:08:44,482 --> 00:08:46,734
I know you've sent him to kill me

95
00:08:46,817 --> 00:08:48,778
because I've already become a loose end.

96
00:09:06,504 --> 00:09:07,922
Why do you look like that?

97
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:39,620
Eat first.

98
00:09:58,848 --> 00:10:00,808
Didn't anyone realize that?

99
00:10:10,276 --> 00:10:11,861
I don't care, sir.

100
00:10:30,338 --> 00:10:31,797
How's your wound?

101
00:10:34,216 --> 00:10:35,051
It's okay.

102
00:10:35,134 --> 00:10:37,178
It's a bit deep though.

103
00:10:37,261 --> 00:10:39,138
It might take a while to heal.

104
00:10:39,722 --> 00:10:41,349
Have you killed him?

105
00:10:42,516 --> 00:10:43,392
No.

106
00:10:46,812 --> 00:10:48,022
You're good.

107
00:10:48,564 --> 00:10:50,358
I know you can do it alone

108
00:10:51,359 --> 00:10:54,111
but you'd be even more formidable if,

109
00:10:54,945 --> 00:10:56,322
you had someone with you.

110
00:10:57,406 --> 00:10:58,658
A partner in crime.

111
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:00,951
Literally.

112
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:06,082
You know, while you're still recovering,
you can stay here.

113
00:11:10,461 --> 00:11:12,338
Daddy, I smell porridge!

114
00:11:16,801 --> 00:11:19,095
Wow, barbie!

115
00:11:21,138 --> 00:11:23,516
Tali, my dear,

116
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:26,519
why don't you go to your room first?

117
00:11:28,062 --> 00:11:30,272
Hi, barbie!

118
00:11:30,356 --> 00:11:32,066
I'm Tali by the way.

119
00:11:33,067 --> 00:11:34,985
May I have some porridge too?

120
00:11:38,614 --> 00:11:40,533
Of course come here.

121
00:11:41,909 --> 00:11:43,536
Tali, my dear

122
00:11:43,619 --> 00:11:45,413
how about this.

123
00:11:45,496 --> 00:11:50,167
You will go to your room
then Daddy will bring you some porridge.

124
00:11:50,793 --> 00:11:52,086
Please?

125
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:01,887
Does it hurt?

126
00:12:08,477 --> 00:12:09,478
Just a little.

127
00:12:09,562 --> 00:12:11,981
Sis, she looks like you.

128
00:12:12,940 --> 00:12:14,567
Come on, let's play.

129
00:12:14,650 --> 00:12:16,777
Let's change her clothes

130
00:12:16,861 --> 00:12:19,447
then let's make her a wound too.

131
00:12:46,807 --> 00:12:49,935
Because of the new
information Mikoy obtained.

132
00:12:56,650 --> 00:12:59,111
This could be very critical

133
00:12:59,195 --> 00:13:01,822
to the case we're building
against the Moraviano.

134
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:25,638
That's valid.

135
00:13:25,721 --> 00:13:27,473
I know where you're coming from,

136
00:13:27,556 --> 00:13:30,100
and I can feel your concern.

137
00:13:40,694 --> 00:13:42,404
Because of that new information.

138
00:13:49,119 --> 00:13:51,664
But we still haven't caught her, sir.

139
00:13:52,623 --> 00:13:54,708
Well, the point is,

140
00:13:54,792 --> 00:13:59,672
all those years of frustration because
you never had a breakthrough in this case.

141
00:13:59,755 --> 00:14:03,175
Now, we're slowly exposing them.

142
00:14:05,678 --> 00:14:08,556
And because of your sacrifices,

143
00:14:08,639 --> 00:14:11,141
we're close to succeeding

144
00:14:11,225 --> 00:14:15,980
and finally getting justice
against the Valtrovis.

145
00:14:16,063 --> 00:14:18,607
We got La Fornarina injured.

146
00:14:18,691 --> 00:14:22,444
Once we catch her, It will be big.

147
00:15:03,694 --> 00:15:06,238
Although I may not agree with it,

148
00:15:06,906 --> 00:15:10,367
but what you did in Prague
was very creative,

149
00:15:11,118 --> 00:15:14,330
and that was what put us here.

150
00:15:17,708 --> 00:15:20,419
I also took some risks against
the Moravianos, just like you.

151
00:15:26,258 --> 00:15:28,636
The day I failed to report to the office,

152
00:15:29,261 --> 00:15:31,472
the truth is I was attacked too.

153
00:15:35,726 --> 00:15:37,811
By one of Moraviano's men.

154
00:15:37,895 --> 00:15:39,104
<i>It's Carlota.</i>

155
00:15:45,986 --> 00:15:47,363
So you're telling me now

156
00:15:47,446 --> 00:15:49,031
you could've been killed!

157
00:15:52,618 --> 00:15:54,119
Why didn't you tell me?

158
00:15:54,703 --> 00:15:56,330
Because I knew you'd get mad.

159
00:15:56,413 --> 00:15:59,041
And, apparently,
I just inherited that from you, sir.

160
00:16:00,042 --> 00:16:01,669
I decided to let her go.

161
00:16:05,089 --> 00:16:08,175
Are you out of your goddamned mind?

162
00:16:09,927 --> 00:16:12,846
I let her go because I know
Viktor will not be happy.

163
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:17,643
So I let her go to prove to her
that Viktor will move against her.

164
00:16:17,726 --> 00:16:19,311
And once that happens,

165
00:16:19,395 --> 00:16:21,063
she will turn against him.

166
00:16:21,647 --> 00:16:25,192
And it's very possible
that I can turn her against Viktor.

167
00:16:32,241 --> 00:16:33,784
That for you to turn her,

168
00:16:35,244 --> 00:16:37,246
that Carlota must survive.

169
00:16:45,754 --> 00:16:48,132
And she's ready to testify
against the Moravianos.

170
00:16:55,431 --> 00:16:57,808
You know, I wanted to get mad
at you at first.

171
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:12,239
Thank you very much.

172
00:17:18,037 --> 00:17:22,458
Looks like the story is finally
starting to go our way.

173
00:17:23,542 --> 00:17:26,045
And in just a few more days, sir,

174
00:17:26,128 --> 00:17:28,130
we'll finally bring down the Moravianos.

175
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:40,934
Guys the PA POP P is
already doing a sound check!

176
00:17:41,018 --> 00:17:43,896
You know, if they just smile at me,
It's already enough for this year!

177
00:17:43,979 --> 00:17:46,815
I'm ready to celebrate
Christmas and New Year.

178
00:17:46,899 --> 00:17:48,525
Who's bias among all of them?

179
00:17:49,276 --> 00:17:51,361
Bias? What is bias?

180
00:17:52,029 --> 00:17:54,865
You know what? Seems like
you don't have Internet, Angelito.

181
00:17:54,948 --> 00:17:56,575
Bias refers to your favorite in a group.

182
00:17:56,658 --> 00:18:00,454
Oh, just like who's my favorite
in <i>Avengers,</i> right?

183
00:18:00,537 --> 00:18:02,539
Just like that.

184
00:18:02,623 --> 00:18:06,460
Actually, I just started
listening to their music.

185
00:18:10,798 --> 00:18:12,466
Even here, there's still an assignment.

186
00:18:12,549 --> 00:18:16,762
I also put an effort here, okay?
Even though I'm not into boy bands.

187
00:18:19,807 --> 00:18:21,892
- You're really sweet!
- So sweet…

188
00:18:21,975 --> 00:18:24,478
- You know what? Let's take a selfie.
- Sofie, wait.

189
00:18:29,441 --> 00:18:35,114
Guys… I think you should just go first.

190
00:18:35,197 --> 00:18:36,573
Huh?

191
00:18:38,492 --> 00:18:39,701
Are you okay?

192
00:18:40,285 --> 00:18:42,162
Why? You don't feel well?

193
00:18:42,246 --> 00:18:43,914
Do you want me to come with you?

194
00:18:44,540 --> 00:18:46,375
No need. I'm okay.

195
00:18:46,458 --> 00:18:51,213
I just need to attend to something urgent
like, right now.

196
00:18:53,674 --> 00:18:55,926
I mean, we can't go
anyway if you're not around.

197
00:18:56,510 --> 00:18:58,137
No worries, just go have some fun!

198
00:18:58,220 --> 00:18:59,763
This is our semestral entrance, right?

199
00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:01,140
All right.

200
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:02,057
- Sofie.
- Sofie.

201
00:19:02,141 --> 00:19:05,060
I'm okay!
I'll wait to hear your stories, okay?

202
00:19:06,979 --> 00:19:08,147
Wait, guys.

203
00:19:18,740 --> 00:19:20,492
<i>Do you really think she knows nothing?</i>

204
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:24,413
That Chiara doesn't know about the world
her mother and father are involved in?

205
00:19:25,581 --> 00:19:27,916
<i>Mikoy, I know you love her.</i>

206
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,127
Don't let yourself be blinded

207
00:19:30,210 --> 00:19:33,255
by your feelings for her
just to believe she's innocent.

208
00:19:33,338 --> 00:19:35,966
<i>That's why I believe</i>
<i>Chiara knows something</i>

209
00:19:36,049 --> 00:19:38,010
<i>and I wouldn't be surprised if one day</i>

210
00:19:38,927 --> 00:19:42,681
she ends up inheriting
the syndicate her family runs.

211
00:19:59,281 --> 00:20:00,490
I'm sorry, ma'am.

212
00:20:00,574 --> 00:20:02,367
Tali can be a bit stubborn.

213
00:20:05,579 --> 00:20:06,788
Actually…

214
00:20:06,872 --> 00:20:09,541
her presence is comforting.

215
00:20:13,587 --> 00:20:14,755
I'm curious.

216
00:20:27,601 --> 00:20:29,811
You consciously chose to raise a child,

217
00:20:29,895 --> 00:20:32,689
in such a chaotic world?

218
00:20:48,622 --> 00:20:50,165
It wasn't hard for me.

219
00:20:51,458 --> 00:20:52,793
Because I fell in love.

220
00:20:52,876 --> 00:20:54,628
I was filled with so much love.

221
00:20:55,212 --> 00:20:59,633
You know that feeling
where you feel like you can do anything?

222
00:21:00,384 --> 00:21:01,969
That's how Tanya and I…

223
00:21:02,052 --> 00:21:03,762
Tali's mother.

224
00:21:04,513 --> 00:21:05,889
Isn't that what they say?

225
00:21:06,473 --> 00:21:08,058
Love conquers all.

226
00:21:09,643 --> 00:21:13,397
It's just that Tanya died
while giving birth to Tali.

227
00:21:14,773 --> 00:21:17,025
But you know, the doctor did warn us

228
00:21:17,109 --> 00:21:19,444
that her pregnancy was risky.

229
00:21:19,528 --> 00:21:22,823
But we were determined
to build a family together.

230
00:21:23,740 --> 00:21:25,325
So even if I'm alone now,

231
00:21:25,951 --> 00:21:27,577
she will be protected,

232
00:21:29,788 --> 00:21:31,957
she will always feel complete with love.

233
00:21:39,881 --> 00:21:41,174
Oh, gosh.

234
00:21:49,016 --> 00:21:50,851
I'll have something like that too.

235
00:22:14,207 --> 00:22:16,960
Hey, hey, hey! Wait, wait, wait!

236
00:22:17,044 --> 00:22:18,795
Angelito!

237
00:22:18,879 --> 00:22:20,505
Angelito, are you okay?

238
00:22:20,589 --> 00:22:22,758
Why are you following! Look what happened!

239
00:22:27,679 --> 00:22:29,222
- You know each other?!
- You know each other?!

240
00:22:31,058 --> 00:22:33,852
Wow, small world!

241
00:22:33,935 --> 00:22:37,647
Out of all the cops,
it turns out you know Agent Kian.

242
00:22:38,356 --> 00:22:41,651
By the way, Sir Kian,
you still remember me?

243
00:22:41,735 --> 00:22:44,905
I'm Angelito, the one you helped before.

244
00:22:44,988 --> 00:22:48,742
Of course. Unfortunately,
we don't have time to catch up today.

245
00:22:48,825 --> 00:22:50,494
We're in a hurry.

246
00:22:50,577 --> 00:22:52,454
He's right, we'll go ahead.

247
00:22:52,537 --> 00:22:53,955
Hold on.

248
00:22:54,039 --> 00:22:55,457
Is this about Mikoy?

249
00:22:55,540 --> 00:22:57,167
Is there something I should worry about?

250
00:22:57,250 --> 00:23:00,629
I can't give any information, Angelito.

251
00:23:01,379 --> 00:23:02,714
Sofie, let's go.

252
00:23:02,798 --> 00:23:05,467
Uh, Angelito,
I'll tell it to you next time.

253
00:23:05,550 --> 00:23:09,346
It's a long story.
And this is not the right place and time.

254
00:23:09,429 --> 00:23:10,931
So I'll go ahead, okay? Bye!

255
00:23:11,014 --> 00:23:12,682
Okay, take care!

256
00:23:27,739 --> 00:23:28,990
Why did you tell him?

257
00:23:29,074 --> 00:23:30,992
He called.

258
00:23:31,076 --> 00:23:34,162
Of course I couldn't resist,
I'm a father too.

259
00:23:34,246 --> 00:23:37,082
I'd also want to know if my child is okay.

260
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:50,595
Thank God.

261
00:23:54,933 --> 00:23:57,644
Are you sure? Because we heard
that you got injured.

262
00:24:00,313 --> 00:24:02,315
You don't need to worry.

263
00:24:02,399 --> 00:24:03,567
Dear…

264
00:24:08,488 --> 00:24:09,781
I'm really okay.

265
00:24:11,867 --> 00:24:12,826
That's why I got caught off guard.

266
00:24:24,045 --> 00:24:25,046
What about that?

267
00:24:25,130 --> 00:24:27,549
Mikoy can't see you while you're injured.

268
00:24:31,803 --> 00:24:33,722
That's okay, I already got it covered

269
00:24:33,805 --> 00:24:38,018
because Mikoy thinks I'm in Prague
so that should give him a few days

270
00:24:38,101 --> 00:24:40,312
and buy me some time to heal up.

271
00:24:40,395 --> 00:24:43,106
When it rains, it pours.

272
00:24:43,190 --> 00:24:45,233
The setbacks just keep coming.

273
00:24:47,777 --> 00:24:49,487
Is there something I should know?

274
00:25:02,292 --> 00:25:04,461
Your chihuahua really can't be trusted.

275
00:25:23,104 --> 00:25:24,940
And I'm sorry, my dear.

276
00:25:35,909 --> 00:25:38,703
<i>What's important is that you find</i>
<i>the agent she's talking to</i>

277
00:25:38,787 --> 00:25:41,456
and that's how you'll find out
where Carlota is.

278
00:25:44,084 --> 00:25:45,335
So…

279
00:25:45,418 --> 00:25:47,087
don't think about this anymore.

280
00:25:48,588 --> 00:25:50,548
<i>Just get some rest, okay?</i>

281
00:25:50,632 --> 00:25:52,884
And heal up, my dear.

282
00:26:12,404 --> 00:26:14,364
Wow, what a fail!

283
00:26:15,657 --> 00:26:19,744
Looks like we don't have
a match for Carlota here.

284
00:26:32,757 --> 00:26:34,134
Just one look.

285
00:26:34,634 --> 00:26:37,387
And I can tell we shouldn't
underestimate that enemy.

286
00:26:40,307 --> 00:26:43,184
CURRENT ROLE:
SENIOR SPECIAL AGENT G.A.G.O.

287
00:26:59,993 --> 00:27:00,827
I know a lot.

288
00:27:00,910 --> 00:27:06,916
<i>We can start from how Viktor got</i>
<i>the throne from Moraviano syndicate.</i>

289
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:11,671
<i>Aren't you curious what Viktor</i>
<i>offered La Morte Bianca</i>

290
00:27:11,755 --> 00:27:14,174
<i>in exchange for all</i>
<i>that protection and power?</i>

291
00:27:22,140 --> 00:27:23,058
Sianong?

292
00:27:29,189 --> 00:27:31,149
I'm working as an asset
for the government.

293
00:27:31,232 --> 00:27:33,360
<i>And I'm helping them build a case</i>
<i>against the Moravianos.</i>

294
00:27:33,443 --> 00:27:37,280
<i>The syndicate suspected</i>
<i>of being run by the Valtrovis.</i>

295
00:27:38,448 --> 00:27:40,075
Mikoy, listen to me carefully.

296
00:27:40,158 --> 00:27:43,411
You need to stay away from Chiara.
You're life is in danger.

297
00:27:43,495 --> 00:27:44,662
Wait, what are you talking about?
